# Gasha, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Gasha (; , Ga≈üa) is a rural locality (a selo) in Alkhadzhakentsky Selsoviet, Kayakentsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 54 as of 2010.
Geography
Gasha is located 27 km southwest of Novokayakent (the district's administrative centre) by road. Alkhadzhakent and Mamaaul are the nearest rural localities.
Nationalities
Kumyks live there.
